│ This calls `createShuffle` which eventually calls the `ShuffleIRBuilder::createShuffleVector` methods that use the current insertion point.                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The issue is that all these instructions are created at the current insertion point set by `setInsertPointAfterBundle`. In our test case, this should be in the entry block since all │
│ ptrtoint instructions are there.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ However, the error suggests that the insertelement instruction doesn't dominate the shufflevector instruction. This could happen if:                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ 1. The insertion point is being changed between creating the insertelement and shufflevector instructions                                                                             │
│ 2. The vector construction logic is creating instructions in different basic blocks                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Looking more carefully at the error, the issue might be that the SLP vectorizer is creating the insertelement instruction as part of building the initial vector, but then the        │
│ shufflevector instruction is being created later when processing a different part of the tree, and the insertion point has changed.                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The fix should ensure that for gather operations, all vector construction happens at a consistent insertion point that dominates all uses.                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Given the complexity of the SLP vectorizer codebase and the specific nature of this bug, the most targeted fix is to ensure that when building vectors for gather operations where    │
│ all scalars are in the same basic block, the insertion point is set to that basic block and not changed during vector construction.                                                   │
